Next, accomplish the following tasks.

From "kubectl" tab,

1. Install Custom Kong plugin for OPA

2. Configure Kong plugin for OPA authorization

NOTE - This applies the Unix Domain Socket(UDS) based configuration. Please refer the `tutorials` section in the Documentation to know how to apply HTTP based configuration

3. Configure OPA to connect to DAS

4. Install Styra Local Plane (SLP)

From "helm values download" tab,

5. Download Helm values.yaml file with OPA sidecar

NOTE - If you're using HTTP based configuration in step 2, please refer to the `tutorials` section in the Documentation to know more about how to apply helm values for HTTP based deployment

Update the Kong deployment to integrate with OPA for authorization
